Viewer discretion is advised.

4
00:00:18,841 --> 00:00:20,841
We’re looking for someone to take care of Day.

5
00:00:20,841 --> 00:00:22,107
He can’t see clearly.

6
00:00:22,107 --> 00:00:24,298
His vision is only 20% effective.

7
00:00:24,298 --> 00:00:25,689
How much do you make a day?

8
00:00:25,689 --> 00:00:27,668
My mom will double it.

9
00:00:28,148 --> 00:00:29,291
Keep your money.

10
00:00:30,285 --> 00:00:31,664
This mouth loves asking for bruises.

11
00:00:32,428 --> 00:00:33,926
Save the money for medical treatment.

12
00:00:34,817 --> 00:00:36,000
What happened to him?

13
00:00:36,493 --> 00:00:39,734
I heard he had a car accident that caused his corneas to be damaged.

14
00:00:39,734 --> 00:00:41,457
His vision has become worse after that.

15
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:46,280
Do you think it's easy for me to take care of you?

16
00:00:47,364 --> 00:00:48,152
Day!

17
00:00:51,383 --> 00:00:52,555
Watch out!

18
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:57,494
He dropped his library membership card.

19
00:00:57,494 --> 00:00:58,406
It’s his.

20
00:00:58,406 --> 00:00:59,554
Let him get it himself.

21
00:01:00,382 --> 00:01:01,732
We don’t need the interview, Mom.

22
00:01:02,538 --> 00:01:03,388
Hire this guy.

23
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:04,640
My name is Mhok.

24
00:01:05,339 --> 00:01:06,586
When should I start?

25
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:07,960
I’ll see you

26
00:01:08,285 --> 00:01:09,049
tomorrow.

27
00:01:23,020 --> 00:01:24,000
Good morning, Mrs. Mhon.

28
00:01:36,556 --> 00:01:39,738
You said casual, didn’t you?

29
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:43,852
Come in.

30
00:01:54,670 --> 00:01:57,232
We have housekeepers here.

31
00:01:57,232 --> 00:01:59,716
Your sole responsibility is to look after Day.

32
00:02:01,133 --> 00:02:02,158
That's a relief.

33
00:02:04,488 --> 00:02:07,440
Your work is eight-to-six, six days a week.

34
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:09,905
If you must stay longer, I'll pay you for the overtime.

35
00:02:10,526 --> 00:02:11,298
Yes.

36
00:02:15,001 --> 00:02:16,198
This is my office.

37
00:02:16,434 --> 00:02:18,537
Don't go in unless it's necessary.

38
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:22,092
And Day's room?

39
00:02:22,413 --> 00:02:23,733
Day’s is over here.

40
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Night’s is on that side.

41
00:02:26,270 --> 00:02:27,679
Mine is on the other wing.

42
00:02:29,148 --> 00:02:30,232
What about their father?

43
00:02:33,368 --> 00:02:34,620
Only the three of us live here.

44
00:02:37,102 --> 00:02:37,850
Oh.

45
00:02:38,175 --> 00:02:38,883
Yes.

46
00:02:40,276 --> 00:02:41,061
Here.

47
00:02:42,509 --> 00:02:43,458
The contract.

48
00:02:43,676 --> 00:02:46,592
If there are no conflicts, sign it and start doing your job.

49
00:02:48,949 --> 00:02:50,200
[55,000 THB per month]

50
00:03:05,721 --> 00:03:09,879
Your main duty is to ensure Day’s safety

51
00:03:10,066 --> 00:03:11,770
and prepare him food.

52
00:03:12,204 --> 00:03:13,057
That’s easy.

53
00:03:13,323 --> 00:03:15,061
I’m the cook when there’s a drinking party.

54
00:03:18,965 --> 00:03:20,433
Day is a picky eater.

55
00:03:20,753 --> 00:03:22,073
He only eats what I make.

56
00:03:24,201 --> 00:03:27,920
Before I go somewhere, I'd cook and put the food in the fridge.

57
00:03:28,298 --> 00:03:29,736
You just need to heat it up for him.

58
00:03:30,238 --> 00:03:31,056
Sure.

59
00:03:32,073 --> 00:03:33,157
Anything else?

60
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:35,102
That’d be all.

61
00:03:37,289 --> 00:03:38,527
Isn't it too little?

62
00:03:39,098 --> 00:03:40,684
Even when I took care of my friend's dog,

63
00:03:40,684 --> 00:03:42,363
I was asked to take it out for a walk.

64
00:03:43,525 --> 00:03:44,358
Please.

65
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,421
Before you take him out for a walk,

66
00:03:46,797 --> 00:03:48,649
make him come out of his room and come downstairs first.

67
00:03:50,152 --> 00:03:53,216
He came downstairs, kicked stuff, and tripped.

68
00:03:53,216 --> 00:03:55,066
He's locked himself up in his room ever since.

69
00:03:59,241 --> 00:04:00,049
Hey.

70
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,677
Can you make coffee?

71
00:04:02,109 --> 00:04:02,906
I can.

72
00:04:02,906 --> 00:04:03,902
Make me one.

73
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,102
Sure.

74
00:04:08,256 --> 00:04:09,361
Night.

75
00:04:09,628 --> 00:04:11,705
Is Day okay with the delegation of authority?

76
00:04:12,662 --> 00:04:13,628
Come on, Mom.

77
00:04:14,037 --> 00:04:16,983
If he agreed to that, we wouldn't need to hire a caretaker, right?

78
00:04:21,513 --> 00:04:22,317
Here.

79
00:04:23,085 --> 00:04:23,867
Thank you.

80
00:04:24,773 --> 00:04:25,800
Take this.

81
00:04:26,502 --> 00:04:28,147
Bring breakfast to Day.

82
00:04:28,645 --> 00:04:30,911
If he hasn't been up, don't wake him.

83
00:04:30,911 --> 00:04:32,240
Just leave it there.

84
00:04:32,624 --> 00:04:33,503
Yes, ma’am.

85
00:04:44,048 --> 00:04:45,265
Don't worry, Mom.

86
00:04:45,442 --> 00:04:48,176
I think Mhok seems okay. It's just his bad-guy look.

87
00:04:48,619 --> 00:04:49,400
Trust me.

88
00:04:50,532 --> 00:04:51,229
Fine.

89
00:04:51,909 --> 00:04:52,976
I'm going to take off now.

90
00:04:53,192 --> 00:04:54,497
Leave me a message if you need anything.

91
00:05:02,937 --> 00:05:03,936
Damn.

92
00:05:04,937 --> 00:05:06,000
He's really bad.

93
00:05:42,354 --> 00:05:44,354
Directed by Noppharnach Chaiyahwimhon

94
00:06:03,975 --> 00:06:05,029
It’s breakfast.

95
00:09:04,094 --> 00:09:06,094
[Self Esteem Bible: Build Your Confidence Day by Day]

96
00:09:39,515 --> 00:09:40,720
[Porjai]

97
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:43,946
Hey, what's up?

98
00:09:44,448 --> 00:09:45,532
Hi.

99
00:09:45,758 --> 00:09:47,196
Have you got fired yet?

100
00:09:48,001 --> 00:09:48,690
No.

101
00:09:49,045 --> 00:09:53,784
Not only still hired, but also paid a very high salary.

102
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:57,862
I just knew that easy jobs with huge pay really existed.

103
00:10:00,001 --> 00:10:01,617
Who was in my room?

104
00:10:02,262 --> 00:10:02,865
Mom!

105
00:10:02,865 --> 00:10:03,760
Hey.

106
00:10:04,352 --> 00:10:05,092
I got to go.

107
00:10:13,249 --> 00:10:14,273
Mom.

108
00:10:16,144 --> 00:10:16,942
What is it?

109
00:10:20,252 --> 00:10:21,099
Who are you?

110
00:10:21,981 --> 00:10:23,419
Ah, it's me.

111
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:25,740
Your new caregiver.

112
00:10:30,047 --> 00:10:31,004
You smell like cigarettes.

113
00:10:34,876 --> 00:10:35,683
Sorry.

114
00:10:37,699 --> 00:10:38,562
This.

115
00:10:40,985 --> 00:10:42,122
Did you do this?

116
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:44,976
Yes, I cleaned it.

117
00:10:45,512 --> 00:10:46,714
Anywhere else you want me to clean?

118
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:49,719
Where is my phone charger?

119
00:10:52,065 --> 00:10:52,797
Right here.

120
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,268
I organized them for you.

121
00:10:55,895 --> 00:10:57,511
So it's easier for you to find.

122
00:10:59,617 --> 00:11:00,435
Here.

123
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,360
This is a tablet charger.

124
00:11:14,899 --> 00:11:15,848
Sorry.

125
00:11:17,723 --> 00:11:18,774
Let me find it for you.

126
00:11:18,774 --> 00:11:19,528
One sec.

127
00:11:22,779 --> 00:11:24,129
Where the hell is it?

128
00:11:25,603 --> 00:11:27,041
Leave my room.

129
00:11:27,573 --> 00:11:28,376
Go.

130
00:11:29,056 --> 00:11:30,017
Leave.

131
00:11:30,164 --> 00:11:31,122
- Leave my room.
- Hold on.

132
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:32,529
- Go.
- What?

133
00:11:33,691 --> 00:11:34,705
Next time,

134
00:11:34,705 --> 00:11:35,845
don't come into my room.

135
00:11:36,282 --> 00:11:38,075
Hey, I just wanted to help.

136
00:11:39,582 --> 00:11:40,405
Leave.

137
00:11:42,347 --> 00:11:43,234
Go!

138
00:11:43,677 --> 00:11:44,790
Didn't you hear me?

139
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:45,796
Fine.

140
00:11:46,086 --> 00:11:47,347
Should I say it again?

141
00:11:54,001 --> 00:11:55,089
Damn it!

142
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:56,480
I meant well.

143
00:11:56,734 --> 00:11:58,734
I was afraid animals would use it as a lair.

144
00:12:00,828 --> 00:12:02,385
Freakin’ silly.

145
00:12:02,721 --> 00:12:04,065
Yeah, right?

146
00:12:04,479 --> 00:12:05,726
Freakin’ silly.

147
00:12:07,950 --> 00:12:09,329
I meant you.

148
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:16,526
Stop poking your nose into other people’s business.

149
00:12:19,751 --> 00:12:21,869
What are you talking about? I don’t do that.

150
00:12:23,035 --> 00:12:24,680
Yeah?

151
00:12:25,319 --> 00:12:27,585
I remember this.

152
00:12:27,765 --> 00:12:32,240
Back when you hit on me, I just said my computer was a little slow,

153
00:12:32,656 --> 00:12:36,814
you had it reset and all my files were gone. Remember that?

154
00:12:38,154 --> 00:12:39,228
So?

155
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:41,159
Your computer worked faster, didn’t it?

156
00:12:43,173 --> 00:12:44,789
Otherwise, you wouldn't like me back.

157
00:12:46,209 --> 00:12:47,795
That’s because I felt pity.

158
00:12:48,766 --> 00:12:50,293
Not for you though.

159
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:52,840
I felt pity for those other girls you might hit on.

160
00:12:55,285 --> 00:12:56,694
Yeah, whatever.

161
00:12:56,955 --> 00:12:58,127
Watch me.

162
00:12:58,773 --> 00:13:01,216
You were soft on me before.

163
00:13:02,096 --> 00:13:03,184
He’s gonna, too.

164
00:13:04,544 --> 00:13:05,781
We’ll see about that.

165
00:13:07,789 --> 00:13:09,789
You’re silly and cocky.

166
00:13:12,340 --> 00:13:13,749
Legs up.

167
00:13:31,171 --> 00:13:33,437
Please open the gate. I forgot my key.

168
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:36,763
Mrs. Mhon. Mr. Night.

169
00:13:38,088 --> 00:13:39,133
Please open the gate.

170
00:13:42,472 --> 00:13:43,634
Can anyone hear me?

171
00:13:43,634 --> 00:13:44,866
Open the door, please.

172
00:13:48,626 --> 00:13:49,442
Hello!

173
00:13:54,791 --> 00:13:55,975
Hey! Somebody's over here.

174
00:14:03,350 --> 00:14:04,362
Are you the new caretaker?

175
00:14:04,983 --> 00:14:05,971
Yeah.

176
00:14:06,699 --> 00:14:07,726
What's your name again?

177
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:09,093
Mhok.

178
00:14:09,678 --> 00:14:11,235
My name is Aon.

179
00:14:11,235 --> 00:14:12,263
I'm blind.

180
00:14:14,627 --> 00:14:15,652
You can't get in, can you?

181
00:14:16,186 --> 00:14:16,910
Right.

182
00:14:17,649 --> 00:14:21,541
Mhok, why don’t you look under the plant pot next to the gate?

183
00:14:33,851 --> 00:14:34,816
Found it.

184
00:14:35,052 --> 00:14:35,732
Great.

185
00:14:36,559 --> 00:14:37,374
Thank you.

186
00:14:38,438 --> 00:14:40,880
Do you work here too?

187
00:14:41,101 --> 00:14:41,955
What? No.

188
00:14:42,428 --> 00:14:47,160
The Shining Society sent me to be a counselor for someone stepping into the world of the blind.

189
00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:48,172
Whoa.

190
00:14:49,241 --> 00:14:50,329
I was trying to sound cool.

191
00:14:50,329 --> 00:14:52,571
Actually, I just come to get free food once a week.

192
00:14:54,207 --> 00:14:55,379
Let's get inside.

193
00:14:55,913 --> 00:14:56,804
All right.

194
00:14:57,188 --> 00:15:01,046
But I'm not sure if Day will let you see him today.

195
00:15:01,628 --> 00:15:03,383
Something happened yesterday.

196
00:15:05,841 --> 00:15:06,786
Master Aon!

197
00:15:06,786 --> 00:15:07,693
Yeah!

198
00:15:07,693 --> 00:15:08,354
Where are you?

199
00:15:16,032 --> 00:15:17,382
- I missed you.
- Me too.

200
00:15:17,382 --> 00:15:19,128
Excuse me. You want anything to eat?

201
00:15:19,128 --> 00:15:21,196
Let’s talk.

202
00:15:21,196 --> 00:15:22,215
Sure.

203
00:15:26,072 --> 00:15:27,776
Oh, wow!

204
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:29,823
He really is a badass, isn’t he?

205
00:15:31,585 --> 00:15:33,171
Just what I need.

206
00:15:33,325 --> 00:15:35,443
Mom will have a long-term negative view toward hiring caretakers.

207
00:15:36,465 --> 00:15:38,849
Well, I’m afraid someone here will too.

208
00:15:39,493 --> 00:15:41,493
Right. You know?

209
00:15:41,645 --> 00:15:45,389
On his first day, he organized my desk and removed everything.

210
00:15:45,901 --> 00:15:48,285
I still haven’t found my charger.

211
00:15:48,711 --> 00:15:50,327
I wonder if he took it and sold it.

212
00:15:51,572 --> 00:15:52,437
Relax.

213
00:15:52,969 --> 00:15:55,464
Adjustment needs time.

214
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:58,715
I give him one week max.

215
00:15:59,006 --> 00:15:59,812
He will quit for sure.

216
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:01,715
No.

217
00:16:02,675 --> 00:16:04,054
I meant you.

218
00:16:05,646 --> 00:16:06,937
Give yourself time.

219
00:16:08,498 --> 00:16:14,133
I know it isn’t easy to spend time with someone with no visual impairment.

220
00:16:18,755 --> 00:16:19,927
Come on, bro.

221
00:16:20,189 --> 00:16:22,189
Who said I wanted to spend time with him?

222
00:16:22,716 --> 00:16:23,480
Well.

223
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:26,844
You never complained about any of your caretakers to me before.

224
00:16:29,487 --> 00:16:30,317
Really?

225
00:16:30,317 --> 00:16:31,191
Yes.

226
00:16:31,689 --> 00:16:33,689
You always let me talk alone.

227
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,172
Is that so?

228
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,127
Speaking of talking,

229
00:16:39,418 --> 00:16:42,216
the other day, I was on Tinder.

230
00:16:44,078 --> 00:16:47,142
I met this girl who was a runner.

231
00:16:47,526 --> 00:16:48,481
Are you serious?

232
00:16:48,954 --> 00:16:51,122
I'm thinking of asking her out for a run.

233
00:16:52,049 --> 00:16:53,428
Just run or something else too?

234
00:16:53,428 --> 00:16:55,976
Well, I'll just see how it goes.

235
00:16:58,772 --> 00:16:59,607
Are you done?

236
00:16:59,607 --> 00:17:00,555
That's right.

237
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,575
I'm done.

238
00:17:03,695 --> 00:17:04,808
Finally.

239
00:17:06,761 --> 00:17:08,406
Oh, hey.

240
00:17:08,406 --> 00:17:09,301
Can I have a selfie with you?

241
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:12,195
Almost forgot that I needed to show this to The Shining Society.

242
00:17:18,921 --> 00:17:20,330
Make sure to look brightened up.

243
00:17:20,715 --> 00:17:23,306
One, two, cheese!

244
00:17:29,376 --> 00:17:30,519
Okay.

245
00:17:30,986 --> 00:17:31,833
And it's done.

246
00:17:33,133 --> 00:17:34,759
Bro, seriously.

247
00:17:34,921 --> 00:17:36,212
Are you really blind?

248
00:17:36,384 --> 00:17:37,675
What?

249
00:17:38,118 --> 00:17:40,029
Blind people have their ways.

250
00:17:40,029 --> 00:17:41,770
That was a super easy skill.

251
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:42,924
Anyone can do that.

252
00:17:45,704 --> 00:17:48,916
If my boss was as good as you, he wouldn't need me.

253
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:51,960
Don't be discouraged yet, Mhok.

254
00:17:52,506 --> 00:17:55,334
Day was a national athlete.

255
00:17:55,773 --> 00:17:57,773
He was a guy with confidence.

256
00:17:58,773 --> 00:18:00,271
But now he's in this condition.

257
00:18:01,329 --> 00:18:02,880
Who would want to leave the house?

258
00:18:04,028 --> 00:18:04,890
Why?

259
00:18:04,890 --> 00:18:06,471
He has me to take care of him now.

260
00:18:06,619 --> 00:18:07,447
What is he afraid of?

261
00:18:07,998 --> 00:18:09,643
He isn't afraid of tripping.

262
00:18:12,327 --> 00:18:14,593
He's afraid of the way people would look at him.

263
00:18:19,347 --> 00:18:22,913
It's scary when we are perceived as…

264
00:18:24,361 --> 00:18:25,449
abnormal people.

265
00:18:33,889 --> 00:18:35,357
There's nothing to be embarrassed of.

266
00:18:36,553 --> 00:18:38,819
You're not in his shoes, you wouldn't get it,

267
00:18:39,174 --> 00:18:39,983
Mhok.

268
00:19:02,398 --> 00:19:03,659
Oh, I've got a question.

269
00:19:04,599 --> 00:19:05,717
Why did Day choose me?

270
00:19:08,761 --> 00:19:09,643
I don't know.

271
00:19:10,732 --> 00:19:17,727
All I know is he bets you won't last a week.

272
00:19:19,551 --> 00:19:21,255
Why is he so confident?

273
00:19:22,493 --> 00:19:24,493
You should be glad, Mhok.

274
00:19:24,493 --> 00:19:28,375
The previous ones couldn't even last three days.

275
00:19:47,701 --> 00:19:48,962
Why did you take off your shirt?

276
00:20:19,922 --> 00:20:20,908
Your lunch.

277
00:20:21,922 --> 00:20:23,111
Leave it by the door.

278
00:20:31,555 --> 00:20:33,031
I'll wait here then.

279
00:20:33,391 --> 00:20:34,176
Call me if you need anything.

280
00:20:35,050 --> 00:20:35,877
Don't wait.

281
00:20:36,066 --> 00:20:37,065
Go wherever you want.

282
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:16,787
I'm right here.

283
00:21:16,787 --> 00:21:17,548
