566
00:43:00,195 --> 00:43:04,733
(“At four o'clock, I shall already be worrying and jumping about.”)

567
00:43:05,182 --> 00:43:08,874
(“I shall show you how happy I am!”)

568
00:43:09,306 --> 00:43:10,592
Give yourself time.

569
00:43:12,044 --> 00:43:17,825
I know it isn’t easy to spend time with someone with no visual impairment.

570
00:43:20,296 --> 00:43:21,300
What are you doing?

571
00:43:21,617 --> 00:43:24,332
Don't you want to know what I look like?

572
00:43:24,747 --> 00:43:25,769
You’re fired.

573
00:44:01,376 --> 00:44:02,477
I’ll get the door.

574
00:44:18,199 --> 00:44:19,183
Who are you here for?

575
00:44:20,796 --> 00:44:21,812
I’m Mhok’s friend.

576
00:44:23,306 --> 00:44:24,090
Ah.

577
00:44:24,645 --> 00:44:25,861
He told me last night.

578
00:44:26,148 --> 00:44:28,306
I’ll transfer the rest to his account and…

579
00:44:28,473 --> 00:44:29,359
Um…

580
00:44:30,364 --> 00:44:31,161
No.

581
00:44:31,919 --> 00:44:33,200
I’m actually here for Day.

582
00:44:45,825 --> 00:44:46,744
This way.

583
00:44:49,282 --> 00:44:50,151
Day.

584
00:44:51,033 --> 00:44:52,531
Mhok sent his friend to see you.

585
00:44:53,188 --> 00:44:56,061
Whatever it is, you can talk to her.

586
00:45:22,856 --> 00:45:24,221
My name is Porjai.

587
00:45:24,597 --> 00:45:25,757
I’m Mhok’s friend.

588
00:45:28,031 --> 00:45:28,871
Yes.

589
00:45:32,271 --> 00:45:34,112
He asked me to give you this.

590
00:45:34,823 --> 00:45:36,426
I don’t know what it is.

591
00:45:38,885 --> 00:45:40,250
Here. Let me.

592
00:45:47,575 --> 00:45:49,575
They are slippers.

593
00:45:50,127 --> 00:45:51,866
It’s a fish.

594
00:45:52,218 --> 00:45:56,016
Wait. A dog, no, a bear, I don’t know.

595
00:45:56,016 --> 00:45:57,151
They’re orange.

596
00:46:18,467 --> 00:46:21,506
He came downstairs, kicked stuff, and tripped.

597
00:46:21,506 --> 00:46:23,537
He's locked himself up in his room ever since.

598
00:46:24,424 --> 00:46:28,195
Because this is what happens if you let him eat by himself.

599
00:46:31,895 --> 00:46:33,102
Ouch!

600
00:46:35,230 --> 00:46:36,004
Serves you right.

601
00:46:36,295 --> 00:46:37,627
Just where I hit it.

602
00:46:42,950 --> 00:46:45,347
That would be all.

603
00:46:45,749 --> 00:46:46,817
I’m taking off now.

604
00:46:46,976 --> 00:46:47,908
Thanks for your time.

605
00:46:53,805 --> 00:46:54,547
Excuse me.

606
00:46:56,026 --> 00:46:56,755
Yeah?

607
00:47:00,799 --> 00:47:01,847
What’s up?

608
00:47:05,308 --> 00:47:07,096
Can you take me to him?

609
00:47:28,446 --> 00:47:30,234
Here we are.

610
00:47:31,588 --> 00:47:33,306
Mhok is sitting right in front of you.

611
00:47:47,063 --> 00:47:49,906
I don't know what happened yesterday.

612
00:47:50,352 --> 00:47:53,833
After he got back, out of nowhere he just blindfolded himself.

613
00:47:54,064 --> 00:47:55,667
He’s slept and eaten here.

614
00:48:00,132 --> 00:48:03,306
I tried to drag him home but he refused.

615
00:48:03,539 --> 00:48:05,936
People think he's lost it.

616
00:48:22,707 --> 00:48:23,568
Hey, you.

617
00:48:25,049 --> 00:48:26,373
What the heck are you doing?

618
00:48:26,706 --> 00:48:27,651
You want to be blind?

619
00:48:29,766 --> 00:48:30,927
I just want to understand.

620
00:48:31,780 --> 00:48:34,467
You think you’d understand me by doing this?

621
00:48:38,932 --> 00:48:39,769
Have a seat.

622
00:49:00,193 --> 00:49:00,956
So.

623
00:49:01,670 --> 00:49:02,907
What have you understood so far?

624
00:49:03,473 --> 00:49:04,500
Tell me.

625
00:49:08,492 --> 00:49:09,465
Oh, I understand.

626
00:49:11,342 --> 00:49:14,294
I understand that I have never understood you at all.

627
00:49:14,665 --> 00:49:16,665
That’s why I said those silly things to you.

628
00:49:18,645 --> 00:49:24,690
Even with my eyes covered, I could feel that the way people looked at me was damn scary.

629
00:49:27,331 --> 00:49:28,096
No.

630
00:49:29,788 --> 00:49:31,393
The way they look isn't scary.

631
00:49:32,705 --> 00:49:36,820
But because we can't see it. We don't know what they think of us.

632
00:49:37,746 --> 00:49:38,794
That's what's scary.

633
00:49:47,034 --> 00:49:49,034
Get out of the way, damn it!

634
00:50:04,855 --> 00:50:06,194
Coming through. Please make the way.

635
00:50:09,235 --> 00:50:12,372
Not to mention I kicked utility poles four times.

636
00:50:14,126 --> 00:50:14,723
Damn.

637
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:16,945
And this is the market I visit every day.

638
00:50:26,144 --> 00:50:26,714
Hey.

639
00:50:29,332 --> 00:50:32,163
I'm sorry for…

640
00:50:34,963 --> 00:50:36,408
being badmouthed.

641
00:50:43,913 --> 00:50:45,543
Get naked and let people watch.

642
00:50:46,498 --> 00:50:48,026
Then I will forgive you.

643
00:50:50,451 --> 00:50:51,304
Are you serious?

644
00:50:51,912 --> 00:50:52,795
Would you do it?

645
00:50:54,792 --> 00:50:56,792
Hey! I’m joking.

646
00:50:58,142 --> 00:50:59,375
Let's save their eyes.

647
00:51:00,932 --> 00:51:02,747
Just take me home.

648
00:51:02,747 --> 00:51:03,697
That's all.

649
00:51:06,004 --> 00:51:06,900
Take you home, huh?

650
00:51:07,799 --> 00:51:08,797
Hell, yeah.

651
00:51:09,442 --> 00:51:10,622
You're my caretaker.

652
00:51:11,492 --> 00:51:12,831
Or should I be the one riding the bike?

653
00:52:04,895 --> 00:52:05,686
Hey.

654
00:52:06,763 --> 00:52:08,448
I need to make a stop and buy something.

655
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:17,549
Hurry up before it's dead.

656
00:52:26,860 --> 00:52:27,765
It’s going in.

657
00:52:27,765 --> 00:52:28,516
Yeah.

658
00:52:28,883 --> 00:52:30,566
One, two, three.

659
00:52:33,257 --> 00:52:34,596
Here we go.

660
00:52:37,282 --> 00:52:38,621
Wow!

661
00:52:38,621 --> 00:52:39,790
Look how happy it is.

662
00:52:40,086 --> 00:52:42,086
Happy to have a new friend, aren’t you?

663
00:52:44,933 --> 00:52:45,746
Oh, wait.

664
00:52:46,063 --> 00:52:47,567
We have to give it a name.

665
00:52:47,739 --> 00:52:49,157
What's the old one's name?

666
00:52:52,487 --> 00:52:53,517
Day…

667
00:52:54,892 --> 00:52:55,392
What?

668
00:52:56,854 --> 00:52:57,938
Little Day.

669
00:53:00,688 --> 00:53:02,133
Night named it.

670
00:53:02,569 --> 00:53:04,172
He bought it and just put it here.

671
00:53:05,015 --> 00:53:06,407
I never wanted to have a fish.

672
00:53:07,232 --> 00:53:08,108
Ah.

673
00:53:08,610 --> 00:53:09,337
Okay.

674
00:53:11,106 --> 00:53:13,106
The old one was named Little Day.

675
00:53:13,831 --> 00:53:16,624
What should we name the new one I bought?

676
00:53:23,307 --> 00:53:24,778
Let's just name it Big Mhok.

677
00:53:27,260 --> 00:53:28,066
No.

678
00:53:28,306 --> 00:53:29,421
It sounds more intimidating.

679
00:53:29,734 --> 00:53:32,025
But the fish’s mouth says ‘I like it.’

680
00:53:33,149 --> 00:53:34,541
Can you say ‘like?’

681
00:53:35,792 --> 00:53:36,919
‘Like.’

682
00:53:37,233 --> 00:53:37,880
Like.

683
00:53:37,880 --> 00:53:38,466
Yes.

684
00:53:38,466 --> 00:53:39,949
See? You like the name too, right?

685
00:53:42,457 --> 00:53:46,810
Big Mhok and Little Day are having a big conversation.

686
00:54:45,039 --> 00:54:45,922
Look.

687
00:54:46,345 --> 00:54:47,145
Come here.

688
00:54:47,673 --> 00:54:49,091
Quickly.

689
00:54:49,091 --> 00:54:50,035
Come. Come.

690
00:54:50,507 --> 00:54:51,668
Come here, Little Day.

691
00:54:51,853 --> 00:54:52,983
Right here.

692
00:54:57,258 --> 00:54:59,390
No more loneliness, Little Day.

693
00:55:27,420 --> 00:55:28,177
Come here.

694
00:55:31,404 --> 00:55:33,404
Come here.

695
00:55:34,138 --> 00:55:35,371
I'm right here.

696
00:56:00,136 --> 00:56:02,136
Directed by Noppharnach Chaiyahwimhon

697
00:56:02,827 --> 00:56:03,462
Ready?

698
00:56:03,462 --> 00:56:04,466
We're having a test.

699
00:56:04,466 --> 00:56:05,378
Phone charger.

700
00:56:05,987 --> 00:56:06,686
Headphones.

701
00:56:10,811 --> 00:56:11,874
Wanna fight?

702
00:56:13,226 --> 00:56:17,106
I'm looking for a book called Last Twilight.

703
00:56:17,106 --> 00:56:18,774
Until the last light goes out.

704
00:56:19,331 --> 00:56:21,066
I know an old bookshop.

705
00:56:21,460 --> 00:56:22,205
Wanna go?

706
00:56:22,786 --> 00:56:26,706
It's the first time I have ever been in a fitting room with someone else.

707
00:56:27,172 --> 00:56:28,590
And do you think I have before?

708
00:56:32,827 --> 00:56:33,690
Day!
